rning Injection into Responses** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/installer.go):\n   - During endpoint registration in `registerResourceHandlers()`, deprecated APIs are identified and their deprecation status is tracked.\n   - The `deprecation.IsDeprecated()` function is called with the current Kubernetes version to determine deprecation status.\n   - Warnings are generated via `deprecation.WarningMessage()` and injected into responses.\n\n5. **Warning Recording and Deduplication** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/warning/warning.go and staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/filters/warning.go):\n   - The `AddWarningsHandler()` function in warning.go adds warnings to request contexts.\n   - The `WithWarningRecorder()` filter in filters/warning.go manages warning deduplication and size limits (4KB total, 256 runes per warning) to ensure responses remain valid.\n   - Warnings are sent as HTTP Warning headers (RFC 7234 code 299) in API responses.\n\n6. **Metrics and Audit Logging** (staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/metrics/metrics.go):\n   - The `deprecatedRequestGauge` metric tracks requests to deprecated APIs by group, version, resource, subresource, and removed_release version.\n   - The `MonitorRequest()` function records deprecated API usage.\n   - The `InstrumentRouteFunc()` wraps route handlers to capture deprecation information.\n   - Audit annotations are added with the removed_release version for compliance tracking.\n\n7. **API Installation and Enforcement** (pkg/controlplane/apiserver/apis.go):\n   - The `InstallAPIs()` method creates a `ResourceExpirationEvaluator` based on the current Kubernetes version.\n   - It calls `RemoveDeletedKinds()` on each API group to remove storage for APIs whose removal version has been reached.\n   - This prevents the API server from serving API versions that are no longer supported.\n\nThese files work together to implement the complete API deprecation policy: detecting deprecated API versions, warning users about their use, preventing removed API versions from being served, and recording telemetry for deprecation enforcement. The policy uses lifecycle interfaces (APILifecycleDeprecated, APILifecycleRemoved, APILifecycleIntroduced, APILifecycleReplacement) implemented via code generation on API types to drive the enforcement decisions."
